From 41059b4cf4d80af5ee4232f483d56b5e80442169 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 18:33:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Restructure into a Python package with a rich-click CLI

Replace the S3-oriented script with an installable package operating on local
files. A framework-agnostic core (pozu_transcode.core) is shared by both CLI
entry points:

- single: transcode one file
- batch:  transcode a directory and emit manifest.json
- survey: report resolutions / aspect-ratio histogram (no transcoding)

Core keeps the canonical encode (faststart, CFR, closed ~1s GOP H.264) and
aspect-ratio bucketing with letterbox padding. Adds pyproject packaging,
unit tests for the geometry/command logic, and a usage README.
