 # Pozu (Transcoding)
 
-Video transcoding for the Pozu project.
+Video transcoding for the [Pozu](https://github.com/CodyCBakerPhD/pozu) pose-labeling
+project.
+
+Pozu pulls random frames from random videos for labeling. To make that lookup fast
+and to give the ML pipeline a single, consistent "pixel space", this tool transcodes
+each source video into a **canonical** form:
+
+- **H.264 High / yuv420p**, broadly browser-decodable and watchable as a normal movie.
+- **`+faststart`** (moov atom at the front) so the browser can seek immediately over
+  HTTP range requests.
+- **Constant frame rate** so `frame = time x fps` is exact.
+- **Closed ~1s GOP** so any random seek decodes at most ~1s of video -- fast random
+  access without all-intra's storage blowup.
+- **Aspect-ratio bucketing**: every video is letterbox-padded (never stretched or
+  cropped) into its nearest-aspect-ratio canvas, giving the model a small set of
+  fixed input sizes at roughly equal pixel area. Black bars cost almost nothing in
+  H.264.
+
+The transcode space is canonical: all labeling, training, and inference run in it.
+
+## Install
+
+Requires **ffmpeg** / **ffprobe** on your `PATH`.
+
+```bash
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+## Usage
+
+```bash
+# 1. Inspect your corpus and confirm the bucket presets fit (no transcoding).
+pozu-transcode survey ./raw
+
+# 2a. Transcode one file.
+pozu-transcode single ./raw/clip.mov ./transcoded/clip.mp4
+
+# 2b. Transcode a whole directory; also writes transcoded/manifest.json.
+pozu-transcode batch ./raw ./transcoded
+```
+
+Common options (shared by `single` and `batch`):
+
+| Option | Default | Meaning |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `--crf` | `20` | x264 quality; lower = better/larger. |
+| `--preset` | `slow` | x264 speed/efficiency tradeoff. |
+| `--gop-seconds` | `1.0` | Keyframe interval; smaller = faster seeks. |
+| `--fps` | `30` | Force CFR to this fps (`0` keeps the source's fps). |
+| `--allow-upscale` | off | Upscale sources smaller than their canvas. |
+| `--bucket NAME:WxH` | built-in set | Override AR buckets (repeatable). |
+
+The default buckets are `sq:720x720`, `4x3:832x624`, `16x9:960x540` (~0.52 MP each).
+Tune them to your data based on the `survey` histogram, e.g.:
+
+```bash
+pozu-transcode batch ./raw ./transcoded \
+  --bucket sq:720x720 --bucket 16x9:960x540 --bucket wide:1024x512
+```
+
+## Manifest
+
+`batch` writes `manifest.json`: one record per output with the canvas, the active
+(non-padding) region, fps, and frame count -- everything the labeler needs to pick a
+random frame, and everything the model needs to mask the bars if desired.
+
+```json
+{
+  "video_id": "clip.mp4",
+  "src_path": "raw/clip.mov", "out_path": "transcoded/clip.mp4",
+  "src_w": 1920, "src_h": 1080, "frame_count": 300,
+  "bucket": "16x9", "canvas_w": 960, "canvas_h": 540,
+  "active_w": 960, "active_h": 540, "pad_x": 0, "pad_y": 0, "fps": 30
+}
+```
+
+## Library API
+
+The CLI is a thin shell over `pozu_transcode.core`, so you can script it directly:
+
+```python
+from pozu_transcode import TranscodeConfig, transcode, transcode_batch
+
+entry = transcode("raw/clip.mov", "transcoded/clip.mp4")
+entries = transcode_batch("raw", "transcoded", TranscodeConfig(crf=18))
+```
+
+## Development
+
+```bash
+pip install -e ".[test]"
+pytest
+```
